  <body>
    <section name="Go to a Document type">
      <span class="shortdesc">How to get to a screen to manipulate a particular document type.</span>

   <script type="text/javascript">
    leftpx=0;
    bottompx=500;
   </script>
   <div class='group'> 
    <div id='screenshot'><div>
     <img src="../../../../images/screenshots/cms_M13/inars/documenttype_card.png" alt='documenttype tab page screenshot'/> 
    </div></div>
    <p>
     Just opened the <a href='../../contributors/concepts/tab_page.html'>tab page</a> for the document
     type 'upcoming' by clicking on its name in the
     <a href='../../contributors/concepts/folder_tabulation_panel.html'>folder tabulation panel</a>.
      The document type 'upcoming' is in the namespace
      'snp'.
      The document type is now shown in <a href='../concepts/review_mode.html'>review mode</a>.
      Change to '<a href='../concepts/edit_mode.html'>edit mode</a>' by clicking the Edit button.

      The 'upcoming' document type is already filled by a structure definition containing the fields:
      Upcoming Date, Title, Indoors?, Recurring?, Entrance price in Euro and Description.
      Upcoming Date is mandatory (this is shown by the * sign).
    </p>
   </div>

   <p>
    To find the right document type, first open the <a href='./goto_namespace.html'>correct namespace folder</a>.
   </p>

